    <div>    <h1 align="center" class="style2">RULES</h1>
      </div>
        <blockquote>
          <p align="left" class="style3">There are certain Rules and Regulations of the hospital are as follows-</p>
          <p align="left" class="style3">1. You are responsible for the following hospital rules and regulations affecting patient care and conduct. </p>
          <p align="left" class="style3">2. This Hospital is a smoke free facility. If this is a problem for you, please discuss your options with your physician. </p>
          <p align="left" class="style3">3. Respect and Consideration, you are responsible for being considerate of the rights of other patients and hospital personnel. This includes assisting in the control of noise and the number of visitors in your room. </p>
          <p align="left" class="style3">4. You are responsible for being respectful of the property of others and of the hospital. Visitors After Visiting Hours Visitors wishing to stay in the hospital after 8:00 PM are asked to check with the nursing staff to obtain a special visitor’s pass. Passes are issued on a 24 hour basis and should be returned to the nurse’s station when the visitor leaves. </p>
          <p align="left" class="style3">5. Entire dues must be clear before discharge. </p>
